George Foot (georgefoot@oxted.demon.co.uk) wrote:
:  
: I should greatly appreciate advice from anyone who has experience in
: connection with hardware rndom number generators and I would particularly
: welcome circuitry and constructional details.
:  

Very easy, George!  Just need a noise diode/gas tube (if you must), an
op amp to bump up the noise signal to 5 volts (ish) and an A/D converter.
Hang this right on the PC bus at port $300 or whatever in the usual way and
read!  Total cost, about 8 quid.

Simon S
